parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure Due to Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake lines due to rust can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a soft or spongy brake pedal, reduced braking ability, and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents or fatalities.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brake pedal travels to the floor
minimal stopping ability
brake failure
use of emergency brake to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, oil temperature gauge, and alternator gauge to stop working, which can lead to the driver being unaware of critical vehicle information, potentially causing accidents or engine damage.

oil temperature gauge
and alternator gauge stop working

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause a fire in the engine well, which can lead to a vehicle fire, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The windshield wiper motor malfunctions
the windshield wiper motor catches on fire
a fire starts in the engine well.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift lever switch can cause the vehicle to stay in the "on" position, which can lead to accidents or unintended vehicle movement.
symptoms: The shift lever switch breaks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially during rain or snow, which can lead to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The windshield wipers stop working suddenly
the windshield wipers operate erratically
the windshield wipers move at high speed without control
the windshield wipers fail to turn off
a loud noise is heard coming from under the hood even when the vehicle is turned off.
